OL,3,CJail for woman who defrauded pensioner
OL,4,Cout of life savings
OL,6,FDuring a sentencing hearing, Judge
OL,7,FLarge said: "You picked up the reigns
OL,8,Fof caring for your elderly neighbour
OL,9,Ffrom your mother but unfortunately, in
OL,10,Fa couple of weeks, you started
OL,11,Fstealing money from him; taking cash
OL,12,Fand using electronic banking to make
OL,13,Ftransfers more than once a day. Over a
OL,14,Ften-month period, you withdrew #700 a
OL,15,Fday.
OL,17,F"#80,000 was used for gambling ` where
OL,18,Fdid the rest go? When the victim
OL,19,Fwanted to see a bank statement, you
OL,20,Ftook the cowardly way out and
OL,21,Ffraudulently altered the statements."
