OL,3,CJail for woman who defrauded pensioner
OL,4,Cout of life savings
OL,6,FIles previously pleaded guilty to two
OL,7,Fcounts of fraud by abuse of position
OL,8,Fand one count of making/supplying an
OL,9,Farticle for use in fraud.
OL,11,FThe 29-year-old was handed a custodial
OL,12,Fsentence of four years and four months.
OL,14,FProceeds Of Crime hearings will take
OL,15,Fplace and a Confiscation Order is
OL,16,Fexpected to be issued which requires
OL,17,Fthe defendant to pay back the
OL,18,Ffinancial gains made from criminal
OL,19,Factivities.
